nvidia-graphics-drivers-418 (418.74-0ubuntu1) eoan; urgency=medium

  * New upstream release:
    - Added a new kernel module parameter,
      NVreg_RestrictProfilingToAdminUsers, to allow restricting the
      use of GPU performance counters to system administrators
      only.
  * debian/templates/nvidia-driver-flavour.docs.in:
    - Install retpoline.html.

 -- Alberto Milone <alberto.milone@canonical.com>  Fri, 10 May 2019 13:26:51 +0200

nvidia-graphics-drivers-418 (418.56-0ubuntu1) disco; urgency=medium

    * New upstream release:
      - Added support for the following GPU:
          GeForce MX230
          GeForce MX250
      - Fixed a bug which could sometimes cause Vulkan applications
        to lock up the     GPU when freeing large chunks of memory on
        systems with PRIME enabled.
      - Updated the driver to restrict use of the GPU performance
        counters to system administrators by default. The previous
        more permissive behavior can be restored by setting
        NVreg_RestrictProfilingToAdminUsers=0 when loading nvidia.ko.

 -- Alberto Milone <alberto.milone@canonical.com>  Mon, 25 Mar 2019 17:01:55 +0100

